SIMPLE: renter
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Renter
<hw>Rent"er</hw> <pr>(r?nt"?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who rents or
leases an estate; -- usually said of a lessee or tenant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Renter
<hw>Ren"ter</hw> <pr>(r?n"t?r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rentered</conjf> <pr>(-t?rd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Rentering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>rentraire</ets>; L. pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>in</ets> into,
in + <ets>trahere</ets> to draw.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sew together
so that the seam is scarcely visible; to sew up with skill and nicety;
to finedraw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To restore the original design of, by working in new
warp; -- said with reference to tapestry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Renterer</ent>⟦br⟧
